<section id="aktiv-biker">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-3">
        <p>Today, TIME is going further in their quest for performance. Following several years of research and the application of three patents, TIME introduces AKTIV, a revolutionary fork featuring an integrated tuned mass damper, which dispels vibrations detrimental to the cyclist's performance and comfort.</p>

        <h3>How does it work?</h3>
        <p>Low frequency vibrations between 25 and 50Hz can have the most detrimental effect on performance causing discomfort and fatigue. Vibrations experienced when cycling fall into this category.</p>
        <p>The tuned mass damper is a dissipative system that is designed to stabilize against Harmonic Vibrations, these occur when the vibration of the bicycle and rider are in phase with the vibrations from the road. Through vibrating itself the Tuned Mass Damper absorbs the worst case vibrations by off-setting the vibrations phase â€“ reducing their intensity.</p>
        <p>Through many tests, TIME have discovered that the fork is the best place to treat harmonic vibrations - it is as close to the road as possible - reducing the effect of all vibration phenomena throughout the system (at the seat post, the pedals and the handlebars).</p>

        

      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-6">
        <%#= image_tag 'aktiv-before-after.png', class: 'img-responsive' %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

